Identification ofb-quark jets One of the most important selection criteria for the analysis of events containing top quarks is the one that identifies jets likely to contain b-hadrons, called b-tagging. Identification of b-jets is based on the long lifetime of b-hadrons, which results in a significant flight path length and leads to reconstructable secondary vertices and tracks with large impact parameters relative to the primary vertex. In this analysis, a neural-network-based algorithm is used at a working point corresponding to a b-tagging efficiency in the simulated tt¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$t\bar{t}$$\end{document} events of 70%, a c-jet rejection factor of 5 and light-flavour jet rejection factor of 140 [67].

