				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\pm 4\%$$\end{document}. Additionally, the mean of the m(jj) distribution is sensitive to the amount of additional radiation. A comparison of the mean value of a Gaussian distribution fitted to the m(jj) distribution in the range of 60GeV<m(jj)<100GeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
