				\begin{document}$$0.68\pm 0.07$$\end{document} for JES correction factor. This deviation of the b-tagging efficiency correction factor from the nominal value of the simulated sample corresponds to a shift of the acceptance in SR1 of 1% and 2.6% in SR2 and SR3. The deviation for the JES correction factor corresponds to a shift of the acceptance of 2.9% in SR1, of 1.4% in SR2, and of 4.4% in SR3. The deviation of the JES correction factor also potentially accounts for differences in the modelling of additional radiation between the different MC event generator set-ups. Finally, the fitted scale factor of the W+\,jets\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
